Text: This is the final lap.
Into the final few laps. The gap for the lead is down to 2.7 seconds 👀
Green flag 🟢 Racing resumes with Max in P2 and 11 laps to go.
A third stop for Max. New Medium tyres 🟡
VSC ⚠️ SAI has stopped on track at Turn 4.
Into the lead goes LEC who gets by Max on fresher tyres. 15 laps to go in Spielberg. https://t.co/xQgt8ijjXm
Lap 51: SAI also pits which moves Max into the lead 👀
Lap 50: LEC pits which moves Max up to P2 👀
📻 "You are free to push." Less than 30 laps to go as Max starts to reduce the gap to the lead ⏱ https://t.co/ks30cXqD3Z
📻 "Box this lap, Max." A second stop and another set of Hards ⚪️ He rejoins in P3 🔧
Approaching half-race distance ⏳ Max has the lead after the first round of stops with LEC right behind 👀 https://t.co/N5vKnNWoH0
Body work damage after contact with RUS is what caused Checo's retirement from this race.
An early end to the #AustrianGP for Checo who is forced to retire at the end of Lap 26 😣
Fastest Lap for Max 🟣 The gap to P2 is down to 13 seconds ⏱
And through! Up to P3 now with both Ferraris in front yet to stop 👀 https://t.co/OUKPRDFL9Y
15 laps complete ✅ Max is working his way through the field on new tyres - next up is HAM in P4 https://t.co/sbCoTGxpri
A new set of Hards for Max who rejoins the race in P8 🔧
📻 "Box this lap, Max."
Here we go! ⚔️
The fight for the lead is hotting up 👀 Less than a second between Max and LEC after eight laps ⏱ https://t.co/6TWw0kQZs2
CONTACT! 💥 Checo collides with RUS at Turn 4, he’s boxed for Hard tyres at the end of Lap 1.
Off we roll for the Formation Lap. Both Bulls will start the #AustrianGP on Medium tyres 🟡
Here we go 💪 Ready to race at the #AustrianGP 🇦🇹 https://t.co/RZ9j33MJhp
